{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, Krajnik et al.",
    "Page 13 of 41 67",
    "(2022) proposed a novel method to reconstruct each part of the human body independently.",
    "It appeared to have smaller errors than other methods, especially in the concave area of the human body.",
    "Unlike single-view body reconstruction, multi-view reconstruction can describe body features from multiple views, which can reduce the error in the prediction of unobservable body parts."
  ]
}